  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to investigate the effect of the enteric hormone Glucagon-like
      Peptide (GLP-2) on patients with short bowel syndrome
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      previous studies have shown that GLP-2 increases mesenteric blow flow, we wish to examine the
      effect of subcutaneus GLP-2 on patients with short bowl syndrome. The patients will single
      blinded been given 450 nmol GLP-2 and isotonic saline in order to act as their own reference.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
